---
import SectionContainer from "../containers/SectionContainer.astro";
import SectionTitle from "../containers/SectionTitle.astro";
import ProjectContainer from "./ProjectContainer.astro";
import ProjectDescription from "./ProjectDescription.astro";
import ProjectDescriptionContainer from "./ProjectDescriptionContainer.astro";
import ProjectExternalSources from "./ProjectExternalSources.astro";
import ProjectImage from "./ProjectImage.astro";
import ProjectTechnologiesContainer from "./ProjectTechnologiesContainer.astro";
import ProjectTitle from "./ProjectTitle.astro";
import reactLogo from "/react.svg";
import nextLogo from "/next-js-blue.svg"
import electronLogo from "/electron.svg"
import tailwindLogo from "/tailwind.svg";
import mysqlLogo from "/mysql-blue.svg";
import cloudinaryLogo from "/cloudinary.svg"
import firenoQuoterImage from "/fireno-quoter-project.webp"
import firenoTrackingImage from "/fireno-tracking-project.webp"
import merchAppImage from "/merch-app-project.webp"
import TechnologieIcon from "./TechnologieIcon.astro";
---

<SectionContainer sectionId="projects" dark>
  <SectionTitle dark>Projects</SectionTitle>
  <ProjectContainer firstProject>
    <ProjectImage image={firenoTrackingImage} description="Logo de github" />
    <ProjectDescriptionContainer>
      <ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
        <TechnologieIcon icon={nextLogo} name="Next" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={reactLogo} name="React" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={tailwindLogo} name="Tailwind" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={mysqlLogo} name="Mysql" />
      </ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
      <ProjectTitle>Fireno Tracking</ProjectTitle>
      <ProjectDescription>
        The software platform allows users to monitor in real time the alerts generated by fire suppression systems, as well as their exact location through the integration of GPS technology. In addition, a friendly user interface was implemented that allows the management of users, devices and companies associated with fire suppression systems.
      </ProjectDescription>
    </ProjectDescriptionContainer>
  </ProjectContainer>
  <ProjectContainer>
    <ProjectImage image={firenoQuoterImage} description="Logo de github" />
    <ProjectDescriptionContainer>
      <ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
        <TechnologieIcon icon={electronLogo} name="Electron" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={tailwindLogo} name="Tailwind" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={mysqlLogo} name="MySQL" />
      </ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
      <ProjectTitle>Fireno Quoter</ProjectTitle>
      <ProjectDescription>
        The software project being described is a quoting tool that allows users to generate a quote for a set of products using prices stored in a database. The software will also allow the user to generate a report in PDF format that includes the detailed quote and the information of the customer for whom it was generated. The quote can be generated in different types of currency (COP, USD, EUR).
      </ProjectDescription>
    </ProjectDescriptionContainer>
  </ProjectContainer>
  <ProjectContainer>
    <ProjectImage image={merchAppImage} description="Logo de github" />
    <ProjectDescriptionContainer>
      <ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
        <TechnologieIcon icon={nextLogo} name="Next" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={reactLogo} name="React" />
        <TechnologieIcon icon={cloudinaryLogo} name="Cloudinary" />
      </ProjectTechnologiesContainer>
      <ProjectTitle>Merch App</ProjectTitle>
      <ProjectDescription>
        The platform consists of generating and previewing designs for items such as sweaters, notebooks or mugs. For the initial design it is possible to use artificial intelligence to generate unique and personalized designs or allow you to upload your own designs. In addition, the platform has intuitive editing tools to further adjust and customize the designs. Once the final prototype is obtained, it is possible to create a preview of the complete collection of items associated with the current design. The tool has localstorage support so it is possible to keep the current design changes and save a list of generated collections.
      </ProjectDescription>
      <ProjectExternalSources projectName="Merch App" githubUrl="https://github.com/MGuerra17/MerchApp" demoUrl="https://merch-app-j3ok.vercel.app/" />
    </ProjectDescriptionContainer>
  </ProjectContainer>
</SectionContainer>
